8.11.2018 || We decided to go hike in the Central Cascades this weekend. The problem; it's a three hour drive out. The solution; sleep closer to the trailhead. The weather was an amazing 75 degrees overnight, with no bugs, no wind, no nothing. Found a nice spot next to a river in the Okanogan-Wenatchee national forest and laid out under the stars. What we didn't know was that the Perseid meteor shower was also in progress, so we got a sweet light show. 
#OkanoganWenatcheeNationalForest #Washington #USA

7.28.2018 || I did this hike up to Camp Muir with two friends some eight years ago. We're started the hike around midday,  we were ill equipped and aside from will power, we didn't have much going. We did make it and for years we talked about how hard the hike was. Fast forward to this last weekend. Isabelle and I had planned for a relaxing weekend in but then changed plans the night before and decided to go for this hike since the weather was nice and we were losing summer daily. I talked up the challenge of the hike with the 5,000 feet of elevation gain, the cold, the thinning air and every other factor that would make this difficult. The next morning we started hiking at 7am and were done before noon. Neither of us thought much of the ascent. Perhaps we built up the arduousness too much in our mind? Either way, preparedness is key. Swipe .
#MtRainierNationalPark #Washington #USA
